HEADWORD: Biblist
<hw>Bib"list</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>bibliste</ets>. See <er>Bible</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>One who makes the Bible the sole rule of
faith.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A biblical scholar; a biblicist.</def> <rj><au>I.
Taylor.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bibracteate</ent>⟦br⟧
